an%2C'%20despite%20its%20lukewarm%20initial%20box%20office%20performance%2C%20gained%20cult%20status%20through%20television%20viewership.%20Actor%20Arshad%20Warsi%20recently%20shared%20amusing%20anecdotes%20about%20the%20film%2C%20revealing%20he%20found%20his%20own%20death%20scene%20comical%20and%20even%20requested%20the%20director%20to%20kill%20off%20his%20character%20early.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Farshad-warsi-reflects-on-cult-classic-jaani-dushman-where-he-was-smiling-during-his-own-death-scene%2Farticleshow%2F115227861.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22These%20Countries%20Offer%20'Assisted%20Dying'%20Or%20Are%20Considering%20It.%20How%20It's%20Done%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESWITZERLAND%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E-%20Switzerland%20legalised%20assisted%20dying%20in%201942%20on%20the%20condition%20the%20motive%20is%20not%20selfish%2C%20making%20it%20the%20first%20country%20in%20the%20world%20to%20permit%20the%20practice.%20Doctors%20can%20prescribe%20drugs%20and%20administer%20them%20or%20had%20them%20over%20for%20self-administration.%20A%20number%20of%20Swiss%20organisations%20such%20as%20Dignitas%20offer%20their%20services%20to%20foreign%20nationals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EUNITED%20STATES%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20Medical%20aid%20in%20dying%2C%20also%20known%20as%20physician%20assisted%20dying%20is%20legal%20in%2010%20states%3A%20California%2C%20Colorado%2C%20Hawaii%2C%20Montana%2C%20Maine%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20Oregon%2C%20Vermont%20and%20Washington%2C%20plus%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia.%20Oregon%20was%20the%20first%20state%20to%20legalise%20it%20under%20a%20law%20which%20came%20into%20effect%20in%201997.%20It%20allows%20mentally%20competent%20patients%20who%20are%20terminally%20ill%20and%20with%20less%20than%20six%20months%20to%20live%20to%20ask%20for%20life-ending%20medication.%20People%20from%20outside%20Oregon%20may%20travel%20to%20the%20state%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20law.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ENETHERLANDS%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E-%20The%20%26quot%3BTermination%20of%20Life%20on%20Request%20and%20Assisted%20Suicide%20(Review%20Procedures)%20Act%26quot%3B%20came%20into%20effect%20in%202002.%20A%20doctor%20is%20immune%20from%20punishment%20for%20euthanasia%20and%20assisted%20suicide%20where%20patients%20are%20experiencing%20%26quot%3Bunbearable%20suffering%20with%20no%20prospect%20of%20improvement%26quot%3B.%20Minors%20can%20request%20euthanasia%20from%20the%20age%20of%2012%20but%20require%20parental%20permission%20before%20the%20age%20of%2016.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBELGIUM%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E-%20Belgium%20legalised%20medically%20assisted%20dying%20in%202002%20for%20the%20terminally%20ill%20and%20for%20people%20experiencing%20unbearable%20suffering%2C%20which%20includes%20patients%20with%20psychiatric%20conditions.%20Since%202014%2C%20those%20under%20the%20age%20of%2018%20who%20are%20terminally%20ill%20are%20covered%20by%20the%20law%20as%20long%20as%20they%20have%20parental%20permission.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ECANADA%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E-%20Canada%20introduced%20%26quot%3BMedical%20Assistance%20in%20Dying%26quot%3B%20in%202016%20for%20those%20whose%20death%20was%20deemed%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Breasonably%20foreseeable%26quot%3B.%20Five%20years%20later%2C%20the%20law%20was%20extended%20to%20permit%20people%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bgrievous%20and%20irremediable%26quot%3B%20medical%20condition%20to%20request%20assisted%20dying.%20The%20country%20has%20delayed%20until%202027%20a%20plan%20to%20extend%20medical%20assistance%20in%20dying%20to%20include%20those%20with%20a%20mental%20illness.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAUSTRALIA%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E-%20Voluntary%20assisted%20dying%20for%20the%20terminally%20ill%20or%20those%20with%20a%20condition%20that%20is%20causing%20intolerable%20suffering%20is%20legal%20in%20most%20Australian%20states%2C%20after%20being%20introduced%20first%20in%20Victoria%20in%202019.%20Doctors%20can%20prescribe%20medication%20for%20self-administration%20or%20administer%20them%20where%20required.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESPAIN%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E-%20Spain%20approved%20a%20law%20in%202021%20which%20allows%20euthanasia%20and%20medically%20assisted%20suicide%20for%20people%20with%20incurable%20or%20debilitating%20diseases%20who%20want%20to%20end%20their%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGERMANY%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E-%20Assisted%20dying%20had%20been%20legal%20in%20Germany%20until%202015%20when%20the%20country%20outlawed%20its%20provision%20on%20an%20organised%20or%20commercial%20basis%2C%20effectively%20banning%20it%20in%20many%20cases.%20Five%20years%20later%20the%20country's%20top%20court%20ruled%20in%20favour%20of%20groups%20providing%20terminally%20ill%20adults%20with%20assisted%20suicide%20services%2C%20but%20lawmakers%20are%20yet%20to%20finalise%20new%20rules.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFRANCE%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E-%20Doctors%20in%20France%20have%20since%202016%20been%20allowed%20to%20put%20a%20person%20who%20is%20close%20to%20death%20and%20in%20great%20pain%20into%20deep%20sedation%2C%20but%20not%20to%20administer%20life-ending%20medication.%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20earlier%20this%20year%20backed%20new%20legislation%20which%20would%20allow%20assisted%20dying%20for%20those%20with%20incurable%20conditions%20and%20a%20bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20April%2C%20but%20elections%20in%20June%20and%20July%20interrupted%20the%20proposed%20law's%20progress.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBRITAIN%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E-%20A%20bill%20to%20allow%20terminally%20ill%20adults%20with%20six%20months%20or%20less%20left%20to%20live%20the%20right%20to%20end%20their%20lives%20was%20introduced%20to%20parliament%20earlier%20in%20October%20and%20will%20be%20debated%20on%20Nov.%