2https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fckgrkg02jz3o.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fckgrkg02jz3o.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UK%20May%20Soon%20Bring%20'Assisted%20Dying'%20Law.%20Lawmaker%20Explains%20Its%20Safeguards%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20proposed%20law%20allowing%20terminally%20ill%20adults%20in%20England%20and%20Wales%20to%20end%20their%20lives%20was%20published%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20setting%20out%20safeguards%20such%20as%20ensuring%20the%20approval%20of%20doctors%20and%20judges%20to%20try%20to%20ease%20concerns%20in%20Britain%20over%20its%20possible%20misuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20law%20has%20polarised%20opinion%20and%20has%20split%20the%20governing%20Labour%20Party.%20Lawmakers%20will%20vote%20on%20the%20proposed%20law%20on%20Nov.%2029%2C%20almost%2010%20years%20since%20parliament%20rejected%20an%20earlier%20bid%20to%20legalise%20assisted%20dying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Labour%20lawmaker%20who%20has%20proposed%20the%20new%20law%2C%20Kim%20Leadbeater%2C%20described%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Bvery%20robust%26quot%3B%2C%20saying%20the%20legislation%20offers%20layers%20of%20safeguards%20to%20protect%20vulnerable%20people%2C%20who%20some%20critics%20fear%20might%20feel%20pressured%20to%20end%20their%20lives%20if%20assisted%20dying%20becomes%20legal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssisted%20dying%20would%20only%20be%20an%20option%20for%20mentally%20competent%2C%20terminally%20ill%20adults%20with%20six%20months%20or%20less%20left%20to%20live%2C%20as%20expected%2C%20under%20the%20proposed%20new%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20safeguards%20include%20two%20doctors%20confirming%20seven%20days%20apart%20that%20the%20person%20is%20eligible%20and%20has%20made%20their%20decision%20free%20from%20pressure%2C%20while%20a%20judge%20would%20then%20speak%20to%20one%20of%20those%20doctors%20before%20a%2014-day%20period%20of%20reflection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20just%20for%20terminally%20ill%20adults.%20It's%20not%20for%20anybody%20else.%20It's%20for%20people%20who%20are%20dying%2C%20and%20it%20is%20about%20shortening%20death%20rather%20than%20ending%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Leadbeater%20told%20BBC%20radio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20would%20make%20it%20illegal%20to%20pressure%20or%20coerce%20someone%20into%20ending%20their%20life%20by%20assisted%20dying.%20The%20offence%20would%20be%20punishable%20by%20up%20to%2014%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20current%20laws%20assisting%20suicide%20is%20punishable%20by%20up%20to%2014%20years%20in%20jail%20but%20Leadbeater%20argues%20that%20current%20rules%20do%20not%20reflect%20a%20shift%20in%20public%20opinion%20over%20the%20issue%20during%20the%20last%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupporters%20of%20assisted%20dying%20say%20Britain%20is%20a%20laggard%20after%20Australia%2C%20Canada%2C%20New%20Zealand%20and%20some%20U.S.%20states%20legalised%20it%20under%20certain%20circumstances%20in%20recent%20years.%20It%20has%20been%20legal%20in%20Switzerland%20since%201942%20and%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20since%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Keir%20Starmer%20has%20said%20politicians%20will%20be%20able%20to%20vote%20with%20their%20consciences%20on%20the%20matter%2C%20rather%20than%20along%20party%20lines.%20He%20has%20supported%20changing%20the%20law%20in%20the%20past%20while%20health%20minister%20Wes%20Streeting%20has%20said%20he%20will%20oppose%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShould%20the%20proposal%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Terminally%20Ill%20Adults%20(End%20of%20Life)%20Members%20Bill%2C%20pass%20a%20first%20vote%2C%20it%20would%20kick%20off%20the%20formal%20process%20for%20a%20law%20change%2C%20subjecting%20it%20to%20further%20scrutiny%20and%20requiring%20approval%20by%20both%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20and%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%2C%20the%20upper%20house%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20British%20lawmakers%20voted%20330%2